---
name: BranchCheckBeforeEdits
description: Require explicit branch verification before implementation edits
alwaysApply: true
---

## Rules

### 1. Check current branch before coding
Before making substantive file edits, run `git branch --show-current` and verify the active branch.

### 2. Report branch context in the workflow
State the current branch name in the working update before substantive edits.

### 3. Enforce branch-scope match
If the active branch does not match the requested feature/fix/change-set scope, create or switch to an appropriate branch first.

### 4. Block implementation on default branches
If the active branch is `main` or `master`, do not begin feature/fix implementation; create a scoped branch first.

### 5. Re-verify branch after switching
After creating or switching branches, re-run `git branch --show-current` before proceeding with edits.
